column5: havn't been able to get out as much as i'd like with work and other things i usually get out on sundays and one day during the week, also try to squeeze a morning or two before work.                first brown from the yak
Some nice fish Miller.  Was good to meet you last month.
Very nice...I used to enjoy your posts on icenews but Tony changed the name and I'm not sure what the site is called now??
nice meeting you too, i'm sure we'll end up fishing together sometime
ifish365.com would be what you're looking for, it caught me off guard too haha
Very nice!!! March was a great month for ya.
Good to hear from you Miller. Nice fish.
sure is! to see you're rod buckle over and look over your shoulder and see a fish flying through the air is definatly an awesome feeling. so far i've just got one but i hope theres many more to come
awesome pictures and a nice variety of fish there!
Good stuff, Miller. Thanks for posting. Thems is some fine looking fish. Oh, and pardon my spelling...it's called my Saturday morning orthography. Thanks again, great fish!
